# FHI-aims geometry.in — crystal structure template
# Example: TiO2 rutile (mp-2657, space group P4_2/mnm, a=4.594 Å, c=2.958 Å)
# Replace lattice vectors and atom positions with the target material.
# Use the get_structure MCP tool to obtain these from the Materials Project.

# --- Lattice vectors (Angstrom) ---
lattice_vector   4.594000   0.000000   0.000000
lattice_vector   0.000000   4.594000   0.000000
lattice_vector   0.000000   0.000000   2.958000

# --- Atom positions (fractional coordinates) ---
# Syntax: atom_frac  x  y  z  Element
# For spin-polarized runs, append:  initial_moment  +/-<value>
atom_frac   0.000000   0.000000   0.000000   Ti
atom_frac   0.500000   0.500000   0.500000   Ti
atom_frac   0.305000   0.305000   0.000000   O
atom_frac   0.695000   0.695000   0.000000   O
atom_frac   0.195000   0.805000   0.500000   O
atom_frac   0.805000   0.195000   0.500000   O
